00:00:00,070 --> 00:00:05,150
This colossal statue shows the power and wealth of its owner,
King Ramses II.

2
00:00:05,550 --> 00:00:13,030
Originally, this statue stood outside the main temple
of the god Ptah in the city of Memphis, the ancient capital of the country.

3
00:00:13,590 --> 00:00:20,150
The purpose of depicting the king in this majestic manner was to
make Ramses the guardian of the sacred precinct of that temple.

4
00:00:20,510 --> 00:00:25,110
We will now see the history of this great king
as he speaks now.
